history.content: 289A (like 260A, 284A, and 286A) are mezzanine courses created primarily to accommodate students in 1-year graduate (masters) programs who have less time to complete their program of study.  All graduate students are able to waitlist these courses until capacity is determined closer to the first day of class.

I'm a graduate student trying to enroll in cs289A, but I get this message whenever I try to do so:

Error:  You are unable to enroll in this class at this time. Available seats are reserved and you do not meet the reserve capacity requirements. If a wait list is available, you may still be placed on the waitlist for this class. To do this, select Add Another Class to return to step 1. Select the class link, select the wait list option and resubmit your request.

The schedule seems to indicate that all seats are open.

Anyone know what's going on?
history.subject: Graduate student, can't enroll in 289A
